  Fruit | Back to Top

   The ovary wall, after fertilization has occurred, develops into a fruit. Fruits may be fleshy,
   hard, multiple or single. View the Seeds of Life site for illustrations and information about
   fruits and seeds. Seeds germinate, and the embryo grows into the next gemeration sporophyte.

